(Thanks to Brian Inglis.)
Document how to detect mktime failure reliably

https://mm.icann.org/pipermail/tz/2024-March/058774.html

Fix .RS/.RE problem in tzfile.5

Problem reported by Alejandro Colomar.

be slightly off, by adding an .RE and removing an .RS, and by
fixing one of the .RS indentings.

Asia/Almaty matches Asia/Tashkent from now on

This pacifies ‘make check_now’.
* NEWS: Mention this.
* zonenow.tab: Remove Asia/Almaty.
* asia: Update Philippine URLs (thanks to Guy Harris).

Port unlikely overflow check to C23

* localtime.c (tzparse): When checking for time_t overflow in the
negative direction, don’t assume that increment_overflow_time (A, B)
preserves *A, because C23-style ckd_add does not do that.
(Problem reported by Dag-Erling Smørgrav.)

* NEWS: Fix typo.  (Thanks to Dag-Erling Smørgrav.)

* tz-link.html: Cite leap-second.file website
(thanks to Martin Burnicki).

* tz-link.html (National histories of legal time): Update Israel
tz history link.  (Thanks to Ephraim Silverberg.)

* theory.html (Leap seconds):
* tz-link.html (Precision timekeeping):

Update a few stale links

(Thanks to Ivan Benovic.)
* tz-link.html: Prefer <code> to <samp> for code snippets.
* tz-link.html: Mention posix_tz_db.

Document POSIX versions more carefully

Since the next POSIX will require support for TZDB Zone names in the
TZ environment variable, be more careful about phrases like
“POSIX-like TZ strings” in comments and documentation.  Call them
“POSIX.1-2017-like TZ strings” instead, to make it clearer that
they’re the traditional POSIX form like TZ='GMT0BST,M3.5.0/1,M10.5.0'
instead of the TZDB form like TZ='Europe/London'.
